reviews.text: Found the customer assistant behind the counter very unhelpful, I was obviously interrupting the time she was spending on her mobile phone . Not a good ambassador for gwr

Small station with a small ticket office.  Helpful staff if you don’t know what ticket you really need.  Also a machine outside for the more seasoned travellers or if the ticket office is closed.

Each platform has a small amount of seating with one shelter, although you can sit in the ticket office too.  There are also bike lock boxes as well on the East bound platform.
Fairly important station between Reading and Newbury with car parking being cheaper than Theale! Part time ticket office. There is a footbridge but no lifts!
Haven't been to the station itself. But we have been standing at the train crossing for 30 mins now. Could be more.
